'''Kamo Shrine''' (かもじんじゃ; also written 賀茂神社 / 加茂八幡宮 / 賀茂八幡宮) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} in Irino, {{ill|lt=Kuroshio|Q1351626|WD=Q1351626}}, {{ill|lt=Hata District|Q1132241|WD=Q1132241}}, {{ill|lt=Kochi Prefecture|Q134093|WD=Q134093}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|UNKNOWN}}, and its former rank under the {{ill|lt=modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|WD=Q712534|lt=modern system}} was {{ill|lt=Gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316}}.

It is the general tutelary shrine of the Irino area, standing inside {{ill|lt=Irino Pine Grove|Q131912175|WD=Q131912175}}, a nationally designated {{ill|lt=Place of Scenic Beauty|Q11414752|WD=Q11414752}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
The enshrined deities are as follows{{Sfn|Meiji Shrine Records|1912}}{{Sfn|Kamo Shrine (Shikinaisha)|1987}}.
* Principal deity: {{ill|lt=Kamo Wakeikazuchi-no-Mikoto|Q11634943|WD=Q11634943|lt=Wakeikazuchi-no-Mikoto}}
* Co-enshrined deity: {{ill|lt=Hachiman|Q261637|WD=Q261637|lt=Hachiman-gū}}
Alternative theories include: {{ill|lt=Ajisukitakahikone|Q506610|WD=Q506610|lt=Ajisukitakahikone-no-Kami}} in ''Shingi Shiryo''{{Sfn|Meiji Shrine Records|1912}}{{Sfn|Kamo Shrine (Shikinaisha)|1987}}; unknown deity in ''{{ill|lt=Jinja Kakuroku|Q11590708|WD=Q11590708}}''{{Sfn|Meiji Shrine Records|1912}}{{Sfn|Kamo Shrine (Shikinaisha)|1987}}; {{ill|lt=Ōkamozumi-no-Mikoto|Q106412720|WD=Q106412720}} in ''Tosa no Kuni Shikisha-kō''{{Sfn|Kamo Shrine (Shikinaisha)|1987}}; and Ōkamozumi-no-Mikoto in ''Henkaimatsufu''{{Sfn|Kamo Shrine (Shikinaisha)|1987}}.

=== History ===
